The paper deals with algorithms for finding maximum flow in planar graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and algorithms. The most relevant sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is the primary category for papers on algorithms. The paper also involves computational geometry, which is covered by cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem of maximum flow can also be viewed as a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper may also involve game theory (cs.GT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) in some aspects.
